      <akn:section eId="sec_42_1904_15">
        <akn:num>42-1904.15</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Revocation of registration; notice; hearing; written finding of fact; cease and desist order as alternative.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_42-1904_15_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_42-1904_15_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>If the Mayor finds after notice and hearing that the declarant has been guilty of a violation for which revocation could be ordered, the agency may issue a cease and desist order instead.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
